des:
If you have any problems, please contact us at support@artika.com

Artika offers the most comprehensive voice controlled smart home experience with Alexa. Control your home lighting and other devices hands free. Just say it, Artika will obey.

Here’s a step by step guide:
(1). Download our "Artika" app in Google Play or iOS App Store;
(2). Launch the app and register a new account (or login if you’re already registered);
(3). Turn on Artika devices and connect them with “Artika” app;
(4). IMPORTANT: You can rename the devices with Artika App, so if you rename a smart bulb “Livingroom Light”, then Echo will record that same name after device is discovered (see step 9);
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from Amazon Market, Google Play or iOS App Store, and connect Echo with "Alexa" app;
(6). Search the Alexa Skills directory for "Artika";
(7). Click Enable skill of "Artika", then input your account username, password and region on the linking page;
(8). Ask Echo:“Alexa,discover devices”. Wait until Echo tells you: "Discover is completed";
(9). Now the setup is complete. Try the different Echo voice commands and enjoy the vocal control of your devices.

Here are a few available voice commands Artika offers:
1. Device control:
* Alexa, turn on my livingroom light
* Alexa, turn off my livingroom light
* Alexa, dim my livingroom light
* Alexa, brighten my livingroom light
* Alexa, set the livingroom light to 20 percent
* Alexa, set bedroom light to green.
* Alexa, set bedroom light to cool white.
2. Scene control:
* Alexa, turn on “evening” (this will activate the smart actions programmed under the “evening” scene).
